column4: Microsoft says game over for Xbox 360

column4: Intel to cut up to 12 000 jobs as PC industry swoons
column5: Intel Corp  said on Tuesday it would cut up to 12 000 jobs globally  or 11 percent of its workforce  as it refocuses its business towards making microchips that power data centers and Internet connected devices and away from the declining personal computer industry it helped found.

column4: Qualcomm profit forecast misses estimates as chip shipments drop
column5: U.S. chipmaker Qualcomm Inc  forecast third-quarter profit below analysts estimates as it expects to ship fewer chips  including those for smartphones  its biggest business.
